Checkout
git checkout <branch-name>

Delete branch
git branch -d <branch-name>

List branch
git branch

Compare
git diff <branch-name-one> <branch-name-two>

git diff branch-name-one..branch-name-two

git diff <commit-hash-one> <commit-hash-two>

Git Stash
Stash is a way to save your changes in a temporary location.
git stash

Stash apply & drop 
git stash pop

Drop stash
git stash drop

Clear stash
git stash clear

Tag
git tag <tag-name>

Annotated tag
git tag -a <tag-name> -m "Release 1.0"

List all tag
git tag

Tagging a hash
git tag <tag-name> <commit-hash>

Push tag
git push origin <tag-name>

Delete tag
git push origin :<tag-name>

Rebase & reflog
Git rebase is a powerful Git feature used to change the base of a branch.
Ensure you are on the branch you want to rebase:

git checkout feature-branch
git rebase main

Git reflog is a command that shows you the history of your commits.

git reflog

git reflog <commit-hash>

Recover lost commits or changes

git reflog <commit-hash>
git reset --hard <commit-hash>










